I kind of like the idea of it, but it does feel a bit bare. The description of the film's contents suddenly ends with an intertitle. Is that all the film that's there? If not, I feel like the researchers would indicate something about what happens after (if it's just blank film, darkness, but they'd note that). Also, it feels a bit odd for them to stop with . Also, it's fairly standard in objects which do something when you observe them that the Foundation notes whether recordings have the same effect, if viewing it through a camera has the same effect, and whether it affects people with given vision issues.

I do like the description of the surreal imagery, although the nature of the film seems to be somewhat self-limiting. Would it work if every group sucked in on a viewing created a new segment with additional film? That would produce a reason to continue studying the film (presumably using D-class or viewing it via camera if such removes the effect) to try to determine who the trapped people are.







